// RULE (NOT yet enforced — EXPECTED TO FAIL until the stdlib is migrated):
//   Everything you import is a DEVICE, so every stdlib module must ship a `.ds.arche` datasheet
//   (its types + any requirements). A stdlib module that is still a bare proc/func module (no
//   datasheet) is not a device. This structural test checks every stdlib module has a datasheet.
//
// Today no stdlib module has a `.ds.arche`, so the check fails and the test FAILS until migration.
// RUN: for m in csv fmt http io net os parse router str term; do test -f %repo/stdlib/$m/$m.ds.arche || { echo "stdlib '$m' is not a device: missing $m.ds.arche"; exit 1; }; done
#import { fmt }
main :: proc() {
  fmt.printf("stdlib_devices_check\n");
}
